The Rev . 
  Robert H . 
  Schuller died early Thursday in California at the age of 88  . 
  He started his ministry in 1955 with $500 from a drive-in movie theater . 
  He built the Crystal Cathedral in Los Angeles to house his TV and radio ministry . 
  In 2013 he was diagnosed with a tumor in his esophagus . 
  He was once a well-known figure on the televangelist circuit . 
  His ministry collapsed in 2011 and he filed for bankruptcy . 
 